Review Comment:
   Looks the original naive c code generates better machine instructions. https://godbolt.org/z/KWrTrWKac
   
   Please note the Arm "add shift" opcode has 2 cycles latency, so the new code is still worse than original one though both contains three machine instructions.
   
   Conditional instructions like `cmov`, `csinc` can easily eliminate this trivial branch.

